2. List all kube contexts
kubectl config get-contexts

select docker-desktop kube cluster
kubectl config use-context docker-desktop

deploy your app to docker-desktop cluster
kubectl apply -f bb.yaml 

find node ip
kubectl get nodes -o wide 
run http://replacewithIpfromabovecommand:30001

delete cluster after use
kubectl delete -f bb.yaml

link: https://docs.docker.com/get-started/kube-deploy/#describing-apps-using-kubernetes-yaml
